<item>
            <title>[SHIRO-205] Filter configs cannot contain commas in INI format</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-205</link>
                <project id="12310950" key="SHIRO">Shiro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider this configuration:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;urls&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    /test/** = roles&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;guest, admin&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The above won&apos;t work at the moment because PathMatchingFilter splits the right-hand value into &apos;roles&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;guest&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;admin&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&apos;. Commas inside square brackets should be ignored when splitting the path value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12478175">SHIRO-205</key>
            <summary>Filter configs cannot contain commas in INI format</summary>
